# FreeSpace 2 or total conversion root folder and executable

In order to be able to launch [FSO][]![][li], the launcher needs to know two things:

* In which folder are the FreeSpace 2 Open (and optionally, FRED 2 Open) executables located
* Which executable it should use

### FS2 or TC root folder

<!-- **TODO try to get rid of the "You must" -- too demanding.** -->

You must select a FS2 or [TC][tc]![][li] root folder before you can select an FSO executable (or [mod][mod]![][li] on the [mods page][modpage]![][li]) to use.

<!-- -- Compound image  of the root folder selection boxa nd button with the"browse for folder" dialog -- -->
 
To select the FS2 or TC root folder, click **Browse...** and browse to the folder containing the FSO executables, then click **Choose** to confirm.  The "Browse for folder" dialog box won't close if the selected folder does not contain valid FSO executables.

### FreeSpace 2 Open (FS2 Open) executable selection

Once you have selected a valid TC root folder, the FS2 Open executable selection box will be populated with each FSO executable found in the TC root folder, branded with the version number, build number (if it's a nightly build), build type and SSE/SSE2 build indication.

